pos_mean_info_list.mean: 破坏的；分裂性的；制造混乱的

bilingual.source: Damage to the axon can disrupt neural communication.
bilingual.target: 轴突的损伤可能会破坏神经通信。

bilingual.source: Overfishing can disrupt the ecological balance of the ocean.
bilingual.target: 过度捕捞会破坏海洋的生态平衡。

bilingual.source: Antibiotics can disrupt the natural microflora of the body.
bilingual.target: 抗生素可能会破坏身体的自然微生物群。

bilingual.source: The army planned raids to disrupt the enemy's supply lines.
bilingual.target: 军队计划进行突袭以破坏敌人的补给线。

bilingual.source: The saboteur cut the power lines to disrupt the event.
bilingual.target: 蓄意破坏者切断了电线以扰乱活动。

bilingual.source: A transposon can disrupt the function of a gene when it inserts itself.
bilingual.target: 当转座子插入时，它可以破坏基因的功能。

bilingual.source: When a species invades a new habitat, it can disrupt the ecosystem.
bilingual.target: 当一个物种侵入新的栖息地时，它可能会破坏生态系统。

bilingual.source: In the lab, sodium dodecyl sulfate is often used to disrupt cell membranes.
bilingual.target: 实验室里经常使用十二烷基硫酸钠来破坏细胞膜。

bilingual.source: It could disrupt the food chains there.
bilingual.target: 这可能会破坏那里的食物链。
同样地，尼古丁会破坏你的睡眠。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, this could disrupt highway and river traffic, but more importantly, could give them the opportunity to destroy vital dams in the region.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可能影响公路和河道交通，但更重要的是这会使他们有机会破坏该地区重要水坝。

yingyinNormal.en: Honey, it's so sweet that you want me to stay, but I can't do that to you. I mean it would disrupt your entire life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要我留下来真的很贴心，但我不能那么做，那会毁了你的生活。

yingyinNormal.en: But Joey, I don't think Ross wants me to move into his apartment and disrupt his life like that. I mean, or he does.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊，我想罗斯不希望我搬过去干扰他的生活，或许他想那么做。

yingyinNormal.en: The perpetrators were targeting the government and their ultimate purpose, though foiled, was to disrupt all mid-Atlantic transportation networks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罪犯的目标是政府，虽然他们的最终目的是干扰大西洋中部的交通网络，但遭挫败。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

disrupt作动词，表示“中断; 扰乱”时，为及物动词，如：
Demonstrators succeeded in disrupting the meeting.
示威者成功地扰乱了会场。

examination_example.sentence: Civilian aviation is being <highlight>disrupted</highlight>, not by the age-old desires for speed romanticism and glamour.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 民航正在受到干扰，不是因为人们对速度、浪漫主义和魅力的长久以来的渴望。

examination_example.sentence: Migrating birds affect ecosystems both at home and at their winter destinations, and <highlight>disrupting</highlight> the traditional routes could have unexpected side effects.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 迁徙的鸟类会影响目前所在地及其冬季目的地的生态系统，破坏传统路线可能会带来意想不到的副作用。

examination_example.sentence: Companies are learning to embrace the technologies as enabling rather than <highlight>disrupting</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公司也正试着接受这些技术，将其视为促进而非破坏。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全四级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Math anxiety can severely <highlight>disrupt</highlight> students' performance in the subject in both primary and secondary school.

examination_example.sentence: The global economy continues to be <highlight>disrupted</highlight> by technology and other massive change.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 全球经济继续受到技术和其他巨大变化的干扰。

examination_example.sentence: It could <highlight>disrupt</highlight> the food chains there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这可能会破坏那里的食物链。
